  "prompt": "What are the expectations of parents from their children?",
  "response": "Parents typically have various expectations for their children, which can vary across cultures and individual families. Here are some common expectations:\n\n1. Education\n- Academic achievement\n- Pursuing higher education\n- Developing knowledge and skills\n- Lifelong learning\n\n2. Personal Development\n- Good character and values\n- Emotional intelligence\n- Self-discipline\n- Resilience and adaptability\n\n3. Career and Professional Success\n- Finding a stable career\n- Financial independence\n- Professional growth\n- Achieving personal goals\n\n4. Moral and Ethical Behavior\n- Honesty and integrity\n- Respect for others\n- Following societal norms\n- Maintaining strong ethical standards\n\n5. Personal Relationships\n- Building healthy relationships\n- Treating family and friends with kindness\n- Finding a suitable life partner\n- Maintaining family connections\n\n6. Health and Well-being\n- Maintaining physical fitness\n- Making healthy lifestyle choices\n- Managing mental health\n- Taking care of personal wellness\n\n7. Social Responsibility\n- Contributing to society\n- Helping others\n- Being environmentally conscious\n- Participating in community activities\n\n8. Independence\n- Making responsible decisions\n- Managing personal finances\n- Problem-solving skills\n- Self-sufficiency\n\nThese expectations can differ based on cultural, social, and individual family backgrounds.",
